attributes.title: Happy Birthday, Indiana!
attributes.caption: Two big reasons to cheer: David and Ryan are back for the second season of the BEST (only) movie-prop-celebrating podcast in the free world, AND Raiders of the Lost Ark is turning 40.
attributes.description: Two big reasons to cheer: David and Ryan are back for the second season of the BEST (only) movie-prop-celebrating podcast in the free world, AND Raiders of the Lost Ark is turning 40. To celebrate, the guys are doing a deep-dive on Indiana Jones whips from all three movies. Plus collecting during COVID, and the latest on their productions House of the Dragon and White House Plumbers. Again Dr. Jones -- we see there is no birthday present you can possess which I cannot take away! Download the audio version:
attributes.show_title: The Stuff Dreams Are Made Of

attributes.title: To The [Lucasfilm] Archives!
attributes.caption: David and Ryan sit down for an exclusive chat with Laela French, the Director of the Lucasfilm Archives.
attributes.description: David and Ryan sit down for an exclusive chat with Laela French, the Director of the Lucasfilm Archives. Laela regales the guys with stories of her 20-year career working in the archives and being surrounded by the most wonderful props, costumes, and models ever made for film, plus the future of the archives and the new Lucas Museum of Narative Art.  Dave shares his own stories of his many, many, many visits to the archives as a fan, a filmmaker, and most recently, an author.  Ryan has no stories to share because he's never been.  Ever.  But he is totally at peace with that.  Really.  I mean it. Download the audio version: https://bit.ly/2SHJERU
attributes.show_title: The Stuff Dreams Are Made Of

attributes.title: Catalog Day: First Blood, Part II
attributes.caption: David and Ryan crack open Prop Store's latest auction catalog to take listeners on a page-turn through the 3-day event featuring nearly 1,400 lots.
attributes.description: David and Ryan crack open Prop Store's latest auction catalog to take listeners on a page-turn through the 3-day event featuring nearly 1,400 lots. This episode has something for every collector: hero Indy hats, stunt Pulse Rifles, fake Playboys from real movies, crew gifts, the furniture catalog from Fight Club, bullet-hit Bat-symbols, Muppet heads, Spinal Tap jackets, pieces from the flawless Richard Gere masterpiece First Knight, and Princess Leia's script from Empire Strikes Back. David even thinks he may have consigned something... maybe... but he can't recall -- which of course is the mark of a true collector. Subotai, thief! Download the audio version: https://bit.ly/3d4Iyqs

attributes.title: It's Ladies' Night
attributes.caption: It's “ladies' night” on The Stuff Dreams are Made Of! Or at least “lady night.”
attributes.description: It's “ladies' night” on The Stuff Dreams are Made Of! Or at least “lady night.”  David and Ryan are joined by an actual lady collector, Nikki Lietzke who talks about HER experiences as a multi-generational Hollywood kid, loving the classics, attending the Debbie Reynolds auction, and collecting movie memorabilia. The three discuss the general dearth of female collectors in the hobby, and wonder why that is.  Sadly though, not even Nikki can explain why David keeps buying monkey-themed hood ornaments from defunct automobile manufacturers. Download the audio version: https://bit.ly/3jsTJx4
attributes.show_title: The Stuff Dreams Are Made Of

attributes.title: Movie Swords!
attributes.caption: Dave and Ryan are joined by real-life movie armorer Tim Lewis to discuss his illustrious career making movie swords for Kingdom of Heaven, Apocalypto, The Old Guard, and the forthcoming House of the Dragon!
attributes.description: Dave and Ryan are joined by real-life movie armorer Tim Lewis to discuss his illustrious career making movie swords for Kingdom of Heaven, Apocalypto, The Old Guard, and the forthcoming House of the Dragon!  Go deep down the scabbard hole for an exhaustive discussion about movie swords, as the guys discuss their favorite sword movies like Conan, Lord of the Rings, Princess Bride, Excalibur and of course the unimpeachable Richard Gere masterpiece First Knight. Download the audio version: https://bit.ly/3ebxjgH

attributes.title: The State of the Collection(s) Address
attributes.caption: David and Ryan discuss their thrilling wins and crushing losses in the recent Prop Store auction while wondering which lunatic spent $238,000 on a space flute, because that person clearly needs help.
attributes.description: David and Ryan discuss their thrilling wins and crushing losses in the recent Prop Store auction while wondering which lunatic spent $238,000 on a space flute, because that person clearly needs help.  These two totally rational and practical collectors of better space objects then take stock of their own collections and talk about what they want to find next, and maybe, just maybe, what might need to go.  Also: the fine art of grudge-bidding. Download the audio version: https://bit.ly/3B2wsbK

attributes.title: GEORGE R. R. MARTIN
attributes.caption: The Stuff Dreams Are Made Of is back! And this time, David and Ryan brought a friend: George R. R. Martin.
attributes.description: The Stuff Dreams Are Made Of is back! And this time, David and Ryan brought a friend: George R. R. Martin. George talks about his life as an ""accumulator"" of many things, like antique toy knights and prop goodies from Beauty and the Beast. The guys also talk collecting comic books and Steve Ditko art, Bayonne pizza, George wanting to possess his own severed head, and, of course—House of the Dragon. No, they did not ask about the book.
attributes.show_title: The Stuff Dreams Are Made Of

attributes.title: Prop Psychology
attributes.caption: David and Ryan lie on the couch while Dr. Shirley Mueller, a licensed psychologist, goes deep inside the collector's brain and attempts to diagnose whatever might be wrong with your hosts.
attributes.description: David and Ryan lie on the couch while Dr. Shirley Mueller, a licensed psychologist, goes deep inside the collector's brain and attempts to diagnose whatever might be wrong with your hosts. Dr. Mueller, a collector herself, explains the unique gift of being a collector and how it leads to a much richer, more colorful life. It all goes quite well until the guys bring up collecting whisky and antique, monkey-themed hood ornaments. Download the audio version: https://bit.ly/3kZuymt
attributes.show_title: The Stuff Dreams Are Made Of

attributes.title: The M41-A Pulse Rifle
attributes.caption: David and Ryan want to introduce you to a personal friends of theirs: the M41-A Pulse Rifle.
attributes.description: David and Ryan want to introduce you to a personal friends of theirs: the M41-A Pulse Rifle. So load up the dropship for a thrilling deep-dive on one of the greatest science-fiction props of all time as they are joined by the two foremost experts on James Cameron's Aliens: Harry Harris and Willie Goldman.  It's the express elevator to hell!  We’re in the pike five by five!  Put her in charge!  Etc. Download the audio version: https://bit.ly/3uNUm83
attributes.show_title: The Stuff Dreams Are Made Of

attributes.title: Movie Guns!
attributes.caption: If the deep dive into the Pulse Rifle wasn’t enough, David and Ryan are devoting their latest show to movie guns!
attributes.description:
If the deep dive into the Pulse Rifle wasn’t enough, David and Ryan are devoting their latest show to movie guns!  Learn what makes a movie gun a movie gun, how movie guns are made, and how to collect them.  To help, they are joined by Jason DeBord, Chief Operating Officer of Julien's Auctions. Jason talks about his life as a connoisseur of movie guns and all things Die Hard and the founding of the Original Prop Blog -- the scourge of movie-prop-scammer scum everywhere. They also chat about one of the most infamous gun movie prop auctions of all time and Jason's favorite superhero movie: Mystery Men. Pew pew.

Download the audio version: https://bit.ly/2X9Nvtj
attributes.show_title: The Stuff Dreams Are Made Of

attributes.title: Catalog Day, Episode III: Revenge of the Bids
attributes.caption: David and Ryan crack open the latest Prop Store catalog to pore over the latest treasures to hit the block.
attributes.description:
David and Ryan crack open the latest Prop Store catalog to pore over the latest treasures to hit the block. They discuss screen-matched Nazi demons, more Aliens props, Spectre rings, Gladiator movies, volleyballs named Wilson, hoverboards, the possibility of David expanding his hood ornament collection, what might be the greatest call sheet of all time, and, of course, one of the hosts’ enduring fascination with Prometheus.

Download the audio version: https://bit.ly/3jlfoGQ

attributes.title: It Belongs in a Museum!
attributes.caption: In the thrilling season two finale, David and Ryan talk museums with Ryan Lintelman, the curator of the Smithsonian's upcoming "Entertainment Nation" exhibit and -- more importantly -- fan of the podcast.
attributes.description:
In the thrilling season two finale, David and Ryan talk museums with Ryan Lintelman, the curator of the Smithsonian's upcoming "Entertainment Nation" exhibit and -- more importantly -- fan of the podcast. Ryan speaks about the plans for the new exhibit and details some of the wonderful film and television pieces in the Smithsonian's collection and the stories behind their acquisition, including the original Scarecrow costume, the original Kermit, most of Indiana Jones's wardrobe, some bad Batman props, and Seinfeld's puffy shirt. I don't wanna be a pirate!
Download the audio version: https://bit.ly/3jKutlj
